{% extends 'base.html.twig' %}

{% block title %}Cookie Policy{% endblock %}

{% block body %}

<style>
    .container {
        max-width: 800px;
        margin: 30px auto;
        padding: 20px;
        box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
    }

    h1 {
        text-align: center;
    }

    h2 {
        color: #333;
        margin-top: 20px;
    }

    p {
        margin: 10px 0;
    }

    a {
        color: #007BFF;
        text-decoration: none;
    }

    a:hover {
        text-decoration: underline;
    }
</style>

<h1>Cookie Policy</h1>
<div class="container">
    
    <p>We use cookies on our website to enhance your browsing experience, analyze site usage, and offer you personalized advertisements. This policy explains what cookies are, the types of cookies we use, and how you can manage your cookie preferences.</p>
    
    <h2>1. What is a Cookie?</h2>
    <p>A cookie is a small text file that is stored on your device (computer, smartphone, tablet) when you visit a website. Cookies allow the website to recognize your device and remember certain information, such as your preferences or items you have added to your cart.</p>
    
    <h2>2. Types of Cookies We Use</h2>
    <br>
    <h4>Essential Cookies</h4>
    <p>These cookies are necessary for the functioning of our website. They allow you to navigate the site and use its features, such as accessing secure areas.</p>
    
    <h4>Performance Cookies</h4>
    <p>These cookies collect information about how visitors use our website, such as the most visited pages. We use this information to improve our site.</p>
    
    <h4>Functional Cookies</h4>
    <p>These cookies allow our site to remember your choices, such as your username or preferred language, to enhance your browsing experience.</p>
    
    <h2>3. How to Manage Your Cookies</h2>
    <p>You can manage your cookie preferences by adjusting your browser settings. Most browsers allow you to block or delete cookies. Please refer to your browser settings for more information.</p>
    <p>Please note that if you choose to disable cookies, some features of our site may not function properly.</p>
    
    <h2>4. Changes to the Cookie Policy</h2>
    <p>We may update this policy from time to time to reflect changes to our cookies or for other operational, legal, or regulatory reasons. We encourage you to review this page regularly to stay informed about our cookie practices.</p>
    
    <h2>5. Contact</h2>
    <p>If you have any questions regarding our cookie policy, please contact us at the following address:
    <a href="mailto:amyaz@contact.fr">amyaz@contact.fr</a></p>
    <br>
    <button class="btn btn-outline-dark rounded-pill" id="reset-consent">Reset Consent</button>

</div>
<script>
document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function () {
    // Existing code to display the popup

    // Click handler for the "Reset Consent" button
    document.getElementById('reset-consent').addEventListener('click', function () {
        deleteCookie('cookie_consent');
        // Optionally: You can also force the display of the popup
        document.getElementById('cookie-consent-popup').style.display = 'block';
    });

    // Function to delete a cookie
    function deleteCookie(name) {
        document.cookie = name + '=; expires=Thu, 01 Jan 1970 00:00:00 GMT; path=/';
    }
});
</script>
{% endblock %}
